text: Erlabrunn is a municipality in Würzburg in Bavaria, Germany, on the left edge of the river Main. It forms an administrative division together with its neighbour Margetshöchheim. Erlabrunn is about north of Würzburg. Its neighbours are in the south Margetshöchheim und Veitshöchheim, in the west Leinach and in the north Zellingen and Thüngersheim. It was first mentioned in 1209. Erlabrunn has had a town twinning arrangement with the French commune Quettehou since 1985. ==References== Category:Würzburg (district)
